Reference docs (reference.docx, reference.pptx) are added in a later step;
pandoc backend falls back to its default styling if a key is missing.

reference.odt exists — it's pandoc's own default reference.odt plus one added
paragraph style, "PageBreak" (fo:break-before="page"), which build_input's
`{=opendocument}` raw block references to force real page breaks between
Pages. ODF has no way to express a page break without a named style, so this
is the minimal reference doc that makes it possible; custom-style class
projection for other classes (hero, content, ...) still falls back to pandoc's
defaults until the real named-style reference doc lands.
